race.comment: Very even. CHELSEA TOFF (8) was solid fresh then returned to winning form last time over 1200m. Fitter again and is a third-up winner. Looks hard to beat again. FLUX (1) was a narrow second two back then fourth but beaten only half a length in richer grade last time. Going very well and this is easier. Deserves to break through. SMOKEY WARRIOR (7) made some progress last start to finish fifth over 1100m at Tatura, beaten 2.25 lengths. Tackles a longer journey this time around and is capable of further improvement. EVERETT (10) has had three runs since a very long break and should be getting to peak fitness now. Has the ability and looks an improver this line-up.
